<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53125h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53125h">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53125h"> 125(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> uncovers / a shoulder in respect,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Et il quitta le ciel. Il mit &agrave; gagner la terre le m&ecirc;me temps qu&apos;un homme fort met &agrave; tendre o&ugrave; &agrave; ployer le bras, et il se trouva devant le Bienheureux. <mark>En signe de v&eacute;n&eacute;ration, il d&eacute;couvrit une de ses &eacute;paules</mark>, il s&apos;agenouilla, il haussa vers le Bienheureux ses mains unies, et il parla: <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 100f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: On the seventh week Brahma, knowing that Siddharta did not really want to do it, came to him and, uncovering one shoulder in respect, persuaded Siddharta to go to Benares and teach the Law. </mm> </dd></dl>
